The regular expression for this problem is:

/^[0-9]{2}-?\w{3}\.[a-zA-Z]{3}$/

Here's a JavaScript function that uses this regex to extract the three character code from the filename:

function extractCode(filename) {
    const pattern = /^[0-9]{2}-?\w{3}\.[a-zA-Z]{3}$/;
    const match = filename.match(pattern);
    return match && match[1];
}

To use this function, simply pass the filename as an argument:

const code = extractCode("57-1Jn.USFM");
console.log(code); // Outputs "1Jn"
